          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Nvidia stocks surge amid Super Micro news</h2>
        </mj-text> 
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/nvidia-stocks-surge-amid-super-micro-news.png" alt="Nvidia's stocks surged after Super Micro announced its data center news" href="https://www.longandshort.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang and Super Micro Computer Charles Liang at the Computex conference in Taipei, Taiwan. Credits: Annabelle Chih/ Bloomberg/ Getty Images
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">On Wednesday, Nvidia’s stock surged 5.1% as Super Micro announced that its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-06-02-2025-h1-1-ai-data-center-systems?source=website" target="_blank">AI data center systems</a> are now ready to ship. The systems are powered by Nvidia’s latest Blackwell chips. The news eased some market concerns relating to Nvidia’s supply chain constraints.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Super Micro provides critical AI data centers that power the AI boom. Nvidia’s chips, which are used to power data centers, remain in high demand. However, the company has faced <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-06-02-2025-h1-2-supply-constriants?source=website" target="_blank">supply constraints</a> in the past as it struggled to ramp up production to keep pace with the skyrocketing market demand.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
